edu.western.java2.review

Class Portfolio

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.western.java2.review.Portfolio

  • public class Portfolio
extends java.lang.Object
    The Portfolio object represents the CD holdings for one or more investors.

    Portfolio is used to summarize investors holdings.

    A portfolio can have several owners, but an owner can only have one portfolio.

    A portfolio can have several CDs associated with it.

    greg
